# interview-simulation

<note id="overview" label="Overview">
## Domain-Specific Interview Simulation

This notebook implements a full interview simulation pipeline based on patent US 2026/0050707 A1 — "Methods and Systems for Domain-Specific Interview Simulations."

### Pipeline
1. **Setup** — Verify environment and install all 6 skills
2. **Configure** — Select interview domain and upload reference documents
3. **Document Intake** — Parse domain documents into structured question banks
4. **Simulation Config** — Set interview parameters (difficulty, question count, thresholds)
5. **Run Interview** — Execute adaptive interview simulation with scoring
6. **Emotion Analysis** — Analyze responses for sentiment and generate avatar emotions
7. **Avatar Rendering** — Render avatar frames with emotional expressions
8. **Response Evaluation** — Detect hallucinations, compute ordinal mappings, score responses
9. **User Profiling** — Update user profile and generate training recommendations
10. **Final Report** — Compile comprehensive interview analysis report

### Skills Used
- `document-intake` — Parse domain documents into question banks
- `interview-simulator` — Core interview orchestration engine
- `emotion-engine` — Sentiment analysis and emotion mapping
- `avatar-renderer` — Avatar facial expression rendering
- `response-evaluator` — Hallucination detection and statistical scoring
- `user-profiler` — Performance tracking and recommendations
</note>

<shell id="check-env" label="Check Environment">
#!/bin/bash
echo "=== Checking Environment ==="

echo "=== Checking uv ==="
if command -v uv &> /dev/null; then
  echo "uv $(uv --version) found"
else
  echo "ERROR: uv is not installed. Install from https://docs.astral.sh/uv/"
  exit 1
fi

echo ""
echo "=== Environment OK ==="
</shell>

<shell id="install-skills" label="Install Skills">
#!/bin/bash
echo "=== Installing Interview Simulation Skills ==="

echo ""
echo "--- document-intake ---"
npx @anytio/pspm@latest add @user/anyt/document-intake -y

echo ""
echo "--- interview-simulator ---"
npx @anytio/pspm@latest add @user/anyt/interview-sim -y

echo ""
echo "--- emotion-engine ---"
npx @anytio/pspm@latest add @user/anyt/emotion-engine -y

echo ""
echo "--- avatar-renderer ---"
npx @anytio/pspm@latest add @user/anyt/avatar-renderer -y

echo ""
echo "--- response-evaluator ---"
npx @anytio/pspm@latest add @user/anyt/response-evaluator -y

echo ""
echo "--- user-profiler ---"
npx @anytio/pspm@latest add @user/anyt/user-profiler -y

echo ""
echo "=== Verify Installed Skills ==="
ls -la .pspm/skills/ 2>/dev/null || echo "Skills directory not found"

echo ""
echo "=== Setup Output Directories ==="
mkdir -p documents question-bank interview-results emotions avatars evaluation profiles reports
echo "Created output directories."
</shell>

<input id="domain-config" label="Interview Domain Configuration">
## Configure Your Interview Simulation

Select the domain and upload reference documents. The system will parse your documents and generate a domain-specific question bank.

&nbsp;

<form type="json">
{
  "fields": [
    {
      "name": "domain",
      "type": "select",
      "label": "Interview Domain",
      "required": true,
      "default": "immigration",
      "options": [
        { "value": "immigration", "label": "Immigration / Visa Interview" },
        { "value": "law", "label": "Legal / Law Enforcement" },
        { "value": "medical", "label": "Medical / Clinical" },
        { "value": "finance", "label": "Finance / Banking" },
        { "value": "education", "label": "Education / Academic" },
        { "value": "custom", "label": "Custom Domain" }
      ],
      "description": "The domain determines the interview context, question style, and evaluation criteria"
    },
    {
      "name": "documentPath",
      "type": "file",
      "label": "Reference Document",
      "required": true,
      "accept": ".pdf,.txt,.md,.docx",
      "multiple": false,
      "description": "Upload a PDF, text, or markdown file containing domain-specific rules, regulations, or procedures"
    },
    {
      "name": "userId",
      "type": "text",
      "label": "User ID",
      "required": true,
      "default": "user001",
      "description": "Unique identifier for tracking performance across sessions"
    },
    {
      "name": "customDomain",
      "type": "text",
      "label": "Custom Domain Name (if Custom selected)",
      "required": false,
      "default": "",
      "placeholder": "e.g., cybersecurity, aviation, real-estate"
    }
  ]
}
</form>
</input>

<task id="document-intake" label="Parse Domain Documents">
Using the **document-intake** skill, parse the reference document from `domain-config`.

1. Read the `documentPath` from `domain-config` input
2. Run the document parser to extract sections, key terms, rules, and definitions
3. Generate a structured question bank with categorized questions at varying difficulty levels
4. Use the `domain` field from `domain-config` (or `customDomain` if "custom" was selected) as the domain context

**Commands:**
```bash
uv run --project .pspm/skills/anyt/document-intake/runtime .pspm/skills/anyt/document-intake/runtime/intake.py \
  --input "{documentPath}" \
  --domain "{domain}" \
  --output question-bank/
```

**Output:** `question-bank/parsed_document.json` and `question-bank/question_bank.json`

After running, display a summary: total questions generated, categories found, and difficulty distribution.
</task>

